There's Francis Ford Coppola
and Andrew Lloyd Webber,

13:32.370 --> 13:35.221
the most surprisingly straight
wine collector in the world.

13:35.223 --> 13:37.056
And he's next to Robert Parker,

13:37.058 --> 13:39.484
who invented the 100-point
wine ranking scale.

13:39.561 --> 13:41.060
I will buy this Napoleon wine

13:41.062 --> 13:43.396
with the money
from the music that I write.

13:43.548 --> 13:46.382
The money from the music
of the night.

13:46.384 --> 13:49.385
I rate this conversation a 36.

13:49.387 --> 13:52.905
Next up is the last known wine
owned by Napoleon.

13:52.907 --> 13:55.224
Offered for sale
by an anonymous owner.

13:55.226 --> 13:56.650
I open the bidding at--

13:56.728 --> 13:58.819
$1 million!

13:58.821 --> 14:00.338
-$1.5 million.
-[phone rings]

14:00.340 --> 14:02.915
Wh-- I'm sorry. I have a call
from my accountant.

14:02.992 --> 14:04.843
Mm-hmm. Mm-hmm.

14:04.919 --> 14:06.069
I bid nothing.

14:06.071 --> 14:08.012
Uh, $1.5 million.

14:08.014 --> 14:09.238
$2 million.

14:09.240 --> 14:12.758
$2 million?
That's, like, 20,000 100s.

14:12.760 --> 14:15.078
Going once. Going twice.
Sold!

14:15.080 --> 14:17.021
[both exclaim]

14:17.023 --> 14:20.083
Slowly, deftly,
losing shall caress you.

14:20.085 --> 14:21.693
Hear it, feel it.

14:21.769 --> 14:23.695
Secretly depress you.

14:23.771 --> 14:25.588
You did<i> Cats,</i> right?

14:25.590 --> 14:27.031
What the hell was that?!

14:27.183 --> 14:29.775
And why do I love it?

14:29.777 --> 14:31.260
We did it!

14:31.262 --> 14:34.688
This money is going to right
so many wrongs.

14:34.766 --> 14:37.100
Thank you, Marge.
For the first time in my life,

14:37.102 --> 14:38.751
I feel free.

14:41.272 --> 14:43.530
You are under arrest
for the high crime

14:43.532 --> 14:45.341
of wine forgery.

15:00.291 --> 15:02.066
♪

15:04.053 --> 15:05.403
Here's your cell.

15:05.480 --> 15:07.647
Does the gentleman
find it suitable?

15:07.799 --> 15:10.325
Why do they always ask the man?

15:12.245 --> 15:15.562
Oh, Homie, Homie, I don't know
how to tell you this,

15:15.582 --> 15:16.915
but I'm in jail.

15:16.991 --> 15:19.325
[chuckles]
Marge in jail? Puh-lease.

15:19.327 --> 15:22.754
This is like that phone scam
I almost fell for last month.

15:22.905 --> 15:24.163
That was really me.

15:24.165 --> 15:25.982
I had to walk home
from the airport

15:26.000 --> 15:27.984
because you wouldn't believe me.

15:27.986 --> 15:29.986
Then this is Marge!
You're in jail?

15:29.988 --> 15:31.245
[crying] Yes.

15:31.264 --> 15:34.991
Waylon and I faked and sold
another Napoleon wine.

15:35.009 --> 15:36.434
Well, this is crazy.

15:36.585 --> 15:39.829
You're in jail for booze,
and I'm...

15:39.831 --> 15:42.273
at home watching the kids.

15:42.350 --> 15:44.091
-Time's up.
-[whimpers]

15:44.093 --> 15:46.611
I've got to go.
I miss you all so much.

15:46.688 --> 15:48.929
-I love you.
-[burps]

15:49.007 --> 15:52.008
Oh, Mommy loves you, too,
Maggie.

15:52.026 --> 15:54.160
